{
  "_comment": [
    "Inbound SIP trunk — defines which DIDs this livekit-sip instance services",
    "and which caller numbers are allowed to reach it.",
    "",
    "Copy to config/sip-inbound-trunk.json (gitignored) and register with:",
    "  lk sip inbound create config/sip-inbound-trunk.json",
    "",
    "Or via scripts/register-sip-routing.sh which is idempotent.",
    "",
    "Fields:",
    "  - `name`            : human-readable label",
    "  - `numbers`         : the DIDs you've pointed at this livekit-sip via",
    "                        Twilio's Origination Connection Policy",
    "  - `allowed_numbers` : caller allowlist. Any caller outside this list is",
    "                        rejected at the trunk before any dispatch rule",
    "                        evaluation. LEAVE EMPTY to accept everyone."
  ],

  "trunk": {
    "name": "twilio-primary",

    "numbers": [
      "+15550000001",
      "+15550000002",
      "+15550000003"
    ],

    "allowed_numbers": [
      "+15559999999"
    ]
  }
}
